270
00:09:38,541 --> 00:09:39,875
[DIABLO gasps]
I'm sorry!

271
00:09:39,958 --> 00:09:41,375
[REM]
You're a Fallen, aren't you?

272
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:42,291
[DIABLO grunts]

273
00:09:42,375 --> 00:09:43,541
[SHERA]
Rem?

274
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:44,791
[footsteps approaching]

275
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:47,625
[grunts] What are you
doing here, Edelgard?

276
00:09:48,583 --> 00:09:49,583
[TAKUMA]
Seriously?

277
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:51,208
Hasn't she
learned her lesson?

278
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:52,250
[DIABLO]
Speak!

279
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,708
Tell me
what you want!

280
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:56,166
I'm not here looking
for a fight today.

281
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:57,500
Just to talk.

282
00:09:57,583 --> 00:09:58,625
We can wait
on the rest.

283
00:09:58,708 --> 00:09:59,625
[REM gasps]

284
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:00,833
[water sloshing]

285
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:02,583
You want to talk?

286
00:10:02,666 --> 00:10:04,166
I received
some information

287
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:05,666
that I had to verify.

288
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:07,333
And now that
I've touched her,

289
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:09,000
I know that it's true.

290
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:11,291
I detect the soul

291
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:14,000
of a Demon Lord within you.

292
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:15,041
[gasps]

293
00:10:15,125 --> 00:10:16,833
[TAKUMA gasps]
Holy crap!

294
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,833
She can actually
sense Krebskulm's soul

295
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:20,000
inside Rem's body?

296
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:21,291
Uh, what now?

297
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:23,500
What's she
going on about, Rem?

298
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:24,708
I kinda feel
like I'm being

299
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:27,166
kept in the dark
on something here.

300
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,208
[SHERA]
So?

301
00:10:29,291 --> 00:10:32,333
♪

302
00:10:32,416 --> 00:10:33,666
You want the truth?

303
00:10:34,708 --> 00:10:37,208
[REM]
Fine, here it is.

304
00:10:37,291 --> 00:10:39,041
The soul of
Demon Lord Krebskulm

305
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:40,916
is sealed
inside of me.

306
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,291
[SHERA]
Huh?

307
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:43,458
[fire crackling]

308
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:46,500
[SHERA]
So that's what's been

309
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:47,666
going on with you.

310
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,000
[REM]
I'm sorry I didn't tell you,

311
00:10:49,083 --> 00:10:50,791
but I thought
it was for the best.

312
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:51,916
It's just....

313
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,833
I didn't wanna
do that to you.

314
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:54,875
To force the burden

315
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:56,541
of my secret
onto your chest.

316
00:10:56,625 --> 00:10:58,541
[SHERA cries]

317
00:10:58,625 --> 00:10:59,791
Shera?

318
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:01,166
[SHERA]
I know I'm not the strongest,

319
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:02,750
but still,
that doesn't mean

320
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:03,958
I don't wanna help you

321
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:05,416
when you're in
some kind of trouble.

322
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,250
You're my friend, Rem.

323
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,458
All this time
must've been

324
00:11:08,541 --> 00:11:09,583
so tough for you.

325
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:11,458
I'm sorry
I never realized it.

326
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:14,291
[REM]
Thank you, Shera.

327
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:15,833
That means a lot.

328
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,541
You're hoping to defeat

329
00:11:18,625 --> 00:11:19,958
the Demon Lord in you,

330
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:20,833
is this right?

331
00:11:20,916 --> 00:11:22,250
That's your plan?

332
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:24,708
[REM sighs]

333
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:26,208
Yeah, it's true.

334
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:27,333
Huh.

335
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:28,458
[REM]
Now that you know,

336
00:11:28,541 --> 00:11:30,750
I want an answer
from you, as well.

337
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:32,083
I always figured
I'd be killed

338
00:11:32,166 --> 00:11:33,750
if a Fallen found out.

339
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:34,875
So I guess
the question

340
00:11:34,958 --> 00:11:37,041
I'm asking you
is, what now?

341
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:39,666
[EDELGARD]
The Demon Lord is delicate.

342
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,916
You can't simply
break its vessel.

343
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,500
There's more
to it than that.

344
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:44,625
So, no.

345
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:45,833
I won't kill you.

346
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:46,833
[DIABLO]
All right.

347
00:11:46,916 --> 00:11:47,666
I'm guessing
you know a way

348
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:48,833
to completely revive

349
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:49,708
the Demon Lord?

350
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:50,833
That's correct.

351
00:11:50,916 --> 00:11:52,500
Really?

352
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:53,750
[EDELGARD]
The resurrection ritual

353
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:56,333
poses zero
risk to her life.

354
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:58,375
It won't harm her.

355
00:11:58,458 --> 00:12:00,875
In fact, it's
the exact opposite.

356
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:02,041
She will be treasured as

357
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:03,666
the mother
of the Demon Lord.

358
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:04,833
Hmm.

359
00:12:04,916 --> 00:12:06,083
You're skeptical.

360
00:12:06,166 --> 00:12:08,000
It's evident that
you don't believe me.

361
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:09,875
I should've
known as much.

362
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:11,666
[sighs]

363
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:12,708
[EDELGARD]
Fine.

364
00:12:12,791 --> 00:12:14,541
I'll teach you
the ritual then.

365
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:15,833
You can conduct it yourself

366
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:17,625
and we Fallen
won't touch you.

367
00:12:17,708 --> 00:12:19,333
How's that?

368
00:12:19,416 --> 00:12:20,375
[TAKUMA]
What do we do?

369
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:21,375
Rem wants to release

370
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:22,583
the Demon Lord's seal

371
00:12:22,666 --> 00:12:24,416
so she can finally
settle the matter.

372
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:27,000
It sucks that Edelgard
discovered her secret,

373
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:28,583
but at least we've got
the same interests

374
00:12:28,666 --> 00:12:30,666
in wanting to get
Krebskulm out of Rem.

375
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:33,666
The real
question though,

376
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,000
is can I beat Krebskulm

377
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:37,458
after the resurrection?

378
00:12:37,541 --> 00:12:39,125
[SHERA]
What do you think, Diablo?

379
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:41,166
[DIABLO]
Very well. Let's do this.

380
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:44,125
Go ahead and
teach me your ritual.

381
00:12:44,208 --> 00:12:46,000
I'll gladly conduct
your ceremony

382
00:12:46,083 --> 00:12:47,708
and see it completed.

383
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:49,291
I'll revive
your Demon Lord,

384
00:12:49,375 --> 00:12:51,291
but only so I can
pulverize the impostor

385
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:52,416
and put him
in the ground!

386
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,083
The Demon Lord Krebskulm

387
00:12:54,166 --> 00:12:55,708
is the real demon lord.

388
00:12:55,791 --> 00:12:57,791
You won't succeed.

389
00:12:57,875 --> 00:13:00,125
Have you already
forgotten my power?

390
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:02,000
♪

391
00:13:08,916 --> 00:13:10,041
Hmm.

392
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:11,125
In three days,

393
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:13,458
on the evening
of the full moon.

394
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:16,166
I'll be waiting for you
at Starfall Tower.

395
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:18,041
We'll conduct
the ritual there.

396
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:19,666
Fine by me.

397
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:21,791
[DIABLO]
We've settled our terms, Rem.

398
00:13:21,875 --> 00:13:22,833
We'll finally be able to

399
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:24,708
free you
from this cursed fate.

400
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:27,750
[DIABLO]
Three days from now,

401
00:13:27,833 --> 00:13:30,208
I'll destroy that
parasite inside you.

402
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:32,625
[STREET CROWD chatter]

403
00:13:33,916 --> 00:13:35,625
[cats meowing]

404
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:41,083
[sniffles]

405
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:43,083
Uh...

406
00:13:43,166 --> 00:13:44,250
So, uh,

407
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,541
are you really
doing this tonight?

408
00:13:46,625 --> 00:13:48,625
[SHERA]
Want some food, Mr. Meowsers?

409
00:13:48,708 --> 00:13:51,125
Ow, no bite!

410
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:52,708
-[sighs]
-[SHERA giggles]

411
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:54,166
Hey, it's Alicia!

412
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:55,125
[ALICIA]
Greetings.

413
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,333
I've just returned from

414
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:57,708
the imperial capital.

415
00:13:57,791 --> 00:13:59,875
I'm relieved to see you
had a safe journey.

416
00:13:59,958 --> 00:14:02,000
Do you just love
the smell of ammonia?

417
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:03,833
[DIABLO] Or did you know
that we were here?

418
00:14:04,875 --> 00:14:06,125
Please, Diablo.

419
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:07,291
Hmm?

420
00:14:07,375 --> 00:14:08,500
I need you to return

421
00:14:08,583 --> 00:14:09,750
to the inn at once.

422
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:10,875
Huh?

423
00:14:10,958 --> 00:14:12,416
[STREET CROWD chatter]

424
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,125
[DIABLO] Do you care to explain
the meaning of this?

425
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:15,291
Did something happen

426
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:16,916
when you were in the capital?

427
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,500
There's a Paladin
named Saddler

428
00:14:18,583 --> 00:14:20,875
lurking somewhere
in this town right now.

429
00:14:20,958 --> 00:14:23,041
Is he dangerous
or something?

430
00:14:23,125 --> 00:14:26,000
I believe his level
as a knight is over 100.

431
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:27,708
Oh?

432
00:14:27,791 --> 00:14:29,625
[TAKUMA]
If this dude's over 100,

433
00:14:29,708 --> 00:14:31,916
then he's on par
with Galford or better.

434
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,875
I've never had any
Paladins come after me

435
00:14:33,958 --> 00:14:35,375
looking for battle in the game,

436
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,875
so I don't know their stats.

437
00:14:37,958 --> 00:14:39,125
To make it worse,

438
00:14:39,208 --> 00:14:40,250
if Saddler believes

439
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,333
there's even a chance

440
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:42,833
that you
worship a Demon Lord,

441
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:45,208
your torture
will be legendary.

442
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:47,041
-Torture?
-[ALICIA] Yes.

443
00:14:47,125 --> 00:14:49,000
He'll drag it out
for as long as possible

444
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:50,750
until you confess.

445
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:52,375
[TAKUMA]
Forget the worshipping,

446
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:53,833
what's he gonna do
to someone who's

447
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:56,750
proclaimed themself
an actual Demon Lord?

448
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,166
[ALICIA]
We should play this safe.

449
00:14:58,250 --> 00:14:59,250
The smart thing to do

450
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:00,708
is for you all
to stay indoors

451
00:15:00,791 --> 00:15:02,916
until Saddler
leaves town.

452
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,166
[TAKUMA]
I knew being a shut-in

453
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,125
would pay off!

454
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:06,208
[REM]
Regardless,

455
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:08,166
I sincerely doubt
that a Paladin

456
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:09,541
could defeat Diablo.

457
00:15:09,625 --> 00:15:12,000
[ALICIA] Of course,
don't mistake my words.

458
00:15:12,083 --> 00:15:14,250
I'm well aware
of Diablo's strength.

459
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:16,416
However, this man,

460
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,291
his true power
is something else.

461
00:15:23,625 --> 00:15:24,416
[gasps]

462
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,083
Ah, there you are.

463
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:27,625
I've been
looking for you.

464
00:15:27,708 --> 00:15:28,958
You just
disappeared on me

465
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:29,916
all of a sudden.

466
00:15:31,166 --> 00:15:32,083
[ALICIA]
You make it out

467
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:33,541
to sound nefarious.

468
00:15:33,625 --> 00:15:34,875
I just wanted
to say hello

469
00:15:34,958 --> 00:15:36,750
to some other
adventurers I know.

470
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,291
[SADDLER]
Is that so?

471
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,291
Pleasure to meet you.

472
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:41,541
The name's Saddler.

473
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,291
I'm a Paladin
of the imperial capital's

474
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,916
Orthodox Church.

475
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,291
And who might you be?

476
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:48,000
[ALICIA grunts]

477
00:15:48,083 --> 00:15:50,416
[TAKUMA] We've gotta
perform the ritual tonight.

478
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,791
I don't have time to risk
provoking this guy.

479
00:15:52,875 --> 00:15:54,166
Just try to
act normal,

480
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:55,666
don't say
anything dumb.

481
00:15:56,625 --> 00:15:58,208
[DIABLO]
I am known as Diablo!

482
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:00,666
The great Demon Lord
from another world!

483
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:01,916
[ALL gasp]

484
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,000
[TAKUMA] Aw, crap.
I acted too normal!

485
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:05,541
[ALL whimpering]

486
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:06,958
[chuckles]

487
00:16:07,958 --> 00:16:10,000
I've been told that
adventurers are known

488
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:11,208
for their
sense of humor,

489
00:16:11,291 --> 00:16:13,125
but to claim that
you're a Demon Lord?

490
00:16:13,208 --> 00:16:15,083
That is just priceless!

491
00:16:15,166 --> 00:16:16,666
-[SADDLER chuckles]
-[ALICIA chuckles]

492
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,208
Diablo's a real prankster,

493
00:16:18,291 --> 00:16:19,958
he's got jokes. [gasps]

494
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:21,541
I don't care
if he's joking,

495
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:23,208
the fact that you can
be friendly with someone

496
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:24,708
who makes light
of a Demon Lord...

497
00:16:24,791 --> 00:16:26,333
I'm afraid
that's a problem

498
00:16:26,416 --> 00:16:28,708
I can't overlook.

499
00:16:28,791 --> 00:16:30,125
[ALICIA]
These adventurers have come

500
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,750
to my aid
when I needed help.

501
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:32,708
I am not ashamed

502
00:16:32,791 --> 00:16:34,125
to call them
my friends.

503
00:16:34,208 --> 00:16:35,166
Hmm.

504
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:36,083
So you're telling me

505
00:16:36,166 --> 00:16:37,750
they have
nothing to hide?

506
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:39,500
Are you planning
to torture me

507
00:16:39,583 --> 00:16:40,750
in order to find out?

508
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,625
I haven't decided yet.

509
00:16:42,708 --> 00:16:44,625
♪

510
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,125
[scoffs]

511
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:48,125
[REM]
This is just ridiculous.

512
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:49,500
Do you have
some kind of issue

513
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:51,375
with us seeing
Alicia Cristela?

514
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:52,875
What the hell
is your problem?

515
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:54,583
[SADDLER grunts]

516
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,458
Pipe down and
remember your place, slave.

517
00:16:58,541 --> 00:16:59,750
[REM gasps]
How dare you,

518
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:01,291
I am not a slave!

519
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:02,875
Maintain
this insolence,

520
00:17:02,958 --> 00:17:05,000
and you'll face
divine judgment.

521
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:06,083
[gasps]

522
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:07,166
You should be the one

523
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,541
apologizing
for being so rude!

524
00:17:08,625 --> 00:17:09,500
Can you
hear yourself?

525
00:17:09,583 --> 00:17:10,416
[gasps]

526
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,208
[REM grunting]

527
00:17:12,291 --> 00:17:13,416
[SHERA]
What's wrong?

528
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,541
-[gasps]
-[SHERA] Rem!

529
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:15,625
[ALICIA]
Are you okay?

530
00:17:15,708 --> 00:17:16,708
[SHERA]
What's happening to her?

531
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:17,416
[SADDLER]
You're feeling the touch

532
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:18,583
of the Gods,

533
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:20,000
a power
bestowed upon me

534
00:17:20,083 --> 00:17:22,875
as a result of my pure,
unyielding faith.

535
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,666
[SHERA] Rem!
Just hang in there!

536
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:26,708
[TAKUMA]
What the hell?

537
00:17:26,791 --> 00:17:28,458
How's he doing this?

538
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:29,666
There was
no power granted

539
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,041
by Gods in the game!

540
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:32,375
What do I do?

541
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:34,000
[grunts]

542
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:35,125
[TAKUMA]
Wait.

543
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:36,708
That thing wrapped
around her head.

544
00:17:36,791 --> 00:17:39,250
Is it...
That's just magic!

545
00:17:40,375 --> 00:17:41,333
[DIABLO]
Cute little stunt

546
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:42,791
you're trying to pull, amateur!

547
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:44,541
-[SADDLER] Amateur?
-[DIABLO] Amateur!

548
00:17:44,625 --> 00:17:45,791
That's divine punishment?

549
00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:47,958
It's nothing
but a simple spell.

550
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:49,583
[groaning]

551
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:51,208
[gasping]

552
00:17:51,291 --> 00:17:52,416
[SHERA]
Rem!

553
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,750
[ALICIA]
Are you all right?

554
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:54,916
[SADDLER]
It takes some audacity

555
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,208
for a mere demon
to insult a Paladin.

556
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:58,333
Talk to me!

557
00:17:58,416 --> 00:18:00,166
Just tell me
you're okay!

558
00:18:01,708 --> 00:18:02,583
I'm okay now.

559
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:03,541
Thank you.

560
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:06,875
[sighs]
Thank goodness.

561
00:18:06,958 --> 00:18:08,000
You dare to question

562
00:18:08,083 --> 00:18:09,541
the power of the Gods?

563
00:18:09,625 --> 00:18:10,625
You must pay
for your doubt

564
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:12,250
through divine punishment.

565
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:13,625
Quit calling it that.

566
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:15,500
We both know
it's pathetic magic,

567
00:18:15,583 --> 00:18:17,375
and it will
not work on me.

568
00:18:17,458 --> 00:18:18,875
Yet another
foolish heretic

569
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:20,416
unwilling to believe.

570
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,750
I'll harden your
doubt and crack

571
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:23,208
it open like a stone!

572
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:25,708
♪

573
00:18:27,083 --> 00:18:28,583
[gasp]

574
00:18:28,666 --> 00:18:31,166
What... is this?

575
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,708
[groans]

576
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:39,000
[BOTH whimper]

577
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:40,250
[exhale]

578
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:41,250
[gasp]

579
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:42,625
[grunts]

580
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,791
[chuckles]
A Cement Lock, huh?

581
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:49,833
Your run-of-the-mill

582
00:18:49,916 --> 00:18:51,375
negative status
Earth spell.

583
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:56,500
Was that
Magic Reflection?

584
00:18:58,833 --> 00:18:59,916
[ALICIA]
So he truly was

585
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,416
just using spells.

586
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,416
[DIABLO]
If I had to guess,

587
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:03,750
he was most likely using

588
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:05,791
Subtle Chant
to cast his spells.

589
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:08,666
A skill accessible
to a level 60 Sorceror.

590
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:09,916
It allows you
to use magic

591
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,125
without speaking
the spell's name aloud.

592
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,541
Is he stuck like that?

593
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,416
When will
the spell wear off?

594
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,333
[DIABLO]
That depends on

595
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:18,666
the caster's level.

596
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:19,958
The magic will eventually

597
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:20,958
dissipate, though.

598
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:23,791
Are you
all right, Rem?

599
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:25,041
Yeah.

600
00:19:25,125 --> 00:19:26,166
Although
I'm starting to get

601
00:19:26,250 --> 00:19:27,833
tired of you
having to save me.

602
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,291
[grunts]

603
00:19:29,375 --> 00:19:30,916
[footsteps departing]

604
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:36,791
Are you sure
it was a wise idea

605
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,958
to allow Saddler
to remain free?

606
00:19:39,041 --> 00:19:40,208
Would you
have preferred

607
00:19:40,291 --> 00:19:41,791
that we kill him instead?

608
00:19:41,875 --> 00:19:42,958
[ALICIA sighs]

609
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:43,916
[DIABLO]
Hmm?

610
00:19:46,791 --> 00:19:47,750
[TAKUMA]
Huh?

611
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,958
What's with the look?

612
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:51,166
[DIABLO grunts]

613
00:19:51,250 --> 00:19:52,666
I couldn't care less

614
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,666
if a peon
lives or dies.

615
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:55,958
If he challenges me again,

616
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:57,375
there will
be no mercy

617
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:58,625
to waste upon him.

618
00:20:00,875 --> 00:20:02,166
That's more like it.

619
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:03,708
I suppose
that I was worried

620
00:20:03,791 --> 00:20:04,583
over nothing.

621
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:05,791
[sighs]

622
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:09,333
[TOWN chattering]

623
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:18,250
[SHERA]
Just about time to leave.

624
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:19,166
[REM]
I know.

625
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:20,458
[footsteps approaching]

626
00:20:21,708 --> 00:20:22,583
You ready?

627
00:20:22,666 --> 00:20:24,125
We should
get going now.

628
00:20:24,208 --> 00:20:25,916
[REM groans softly]

629
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:29,208
What's the matter, Rem?

630
00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:30,416
I feel like
we should

631
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,250
tell her the truth.

632
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:34,125
You mean Alicia?

633
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,583
[REM sighs]

634
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:36,833
[SHERA]
I think that'd be okay.

635
00:20:36,916 --> 00:20:37,750
[gasps]

636
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:38,833
We already know

637
00:20:38,916 --> 00:20:40,208
Alicia's a good person.

638
00:20:40,291 --> 00:20:41,833
I'm sure that
she'd understand.

639
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,750
-[DIABLO] I have to disagree.
-[BOTH gasp]

640
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:48,000
Regardless,
she's an imperial knight.

641
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:48,958
Considering that,

642
00:20:49,041 --> 00:20:50,125
she won't overlook

643
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,500
the Demon Lord's revival.

644
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,291
I understand
what you're saying,

645
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:55,041
but, still.

646
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:56,083
Hmm.

647
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:57,791
[REM]
Even if you're right.

648
00:20:57,875 --> 00:21:00,375
I want to trust Alicia.

649
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:01,750
She's become my friend,

650
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,791
the same way
you and Shera have.

651
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:06,708
So I'm willing to
take the chance.

652
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:11,333
[REM and SHERA sigh]

653
00:21:11,416 --> 00:21:13,500
Thank you
for telling me.

654
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:15,125
I can't imagine how much

655
00:21:15,208 --> 00:21:17,333
you've had to
suffer with this.

656
00:21:17,416 --> 00:21:18,708
Then to
confess to me?

657
00:21:18,791 --> 00:21:21,166
It must've been difficult.

658
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:23,500
I'll help you
as much as I can.

659
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:24,541
There's no
need for you

660
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:25,875
to bear such
an awful burden

661
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:26,958
on your own.

662
00:21:27,041 --> 00:21:28,250
-I'm here for you.
-[REM gasps]

663
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:30,541
[ALICIA]
We are friends, after all.

664
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:31,750
Thank you, Alicia.

665
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,583
Thank you so much.

666
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:34,625
[whimpers]

667
00:21:34,708 --> 00:21:36,041
[cries]

668
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:38,833
[TAKUMA]
Why does this feel

669
00:21:38,916 --> 00:21:40,666
so cheap to me?

670
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,125
Something's off here.

671
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:43,250
Seriously.

672
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:44,541
What's this
uneasy feeling

673
00:21:44,625 --> 00:21:46,125
in my chest?

674
00:21:46,208 --> 00:21:47,708
[grunts]
No, no, shake it off!

675
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:48,750
I'm just exhibiting what

676
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:50,416
social people
call feelings.

677
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,416
No reason for me to go
and freak out over it.

678
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,291
No.

679
00:21:53,375 --> 00:21:56,500
♪

680
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,250
Soon,
my Demon Lord.

681
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:04,958
The time is upon us,

682
00:22:05,041 --> 00:22:06,916
for your rebirth.

683
00:23:37,083 --> 00:23:38,416
[KREBSKULM]
Are you the fools

684
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:39,500
who have woken me

685
00:23:39,583 --> 00:23:40,541
from my slumber?

686
00:23:40,625 --> 00:23:41,750
[TAKUMA]
That's the Demon Lord?

687
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:43,125
[MAN]
This incomplete Demon Lord

688
00:23:43,208 --> 00:23:44,125
must die!

689
00:23:44,208 --> 00:23:45,125
[REM]
Please save me from

690
00:23:45,208 --> 00:23:46,250
this terrible fate.

